Ok, so the first problem I see in {{zk::ZooKeeperAdapter::getNodeData}}:

{code}
        // This...
        return string( buffer, buffer + len );
        // ... should be this:
        // return string( buffer, len );
{code}

The existing code was passing the length of the data _plus_ the pointer to the buffer, but that second argument is supposed to be just the length.

After correcting that and hitting my breakpoint on {{zk::ZooKeeperAdapter::getNodeData}} a second time, we're now trying to get the node data for path {{"/admin"}}. This then fails as as {{zoo_get}} sets {{len = -1}}. From reading {{zookeeper.h}}, it looks like the {{buffer_len}} param will be set to {{-1}} when the data is "null". For the purposes of {{zkfuse}}, I imagine that we want to check if {{len == -1}} and return an empty string if so.

After fixing those problems, I now fail with: {{zkfuse: zkfuse.cc:2258: int ZkFuseFile::update(bool): Assertion `newFile == false || _isOnlyRegOpen()' failed.}}

Still poking around...

Actually, I can't reproduce that assertion. This patch should fix the bug:

{code}
diff --git a/src/contrib/zkfuse/src/zkadapter.cc b/src/contrib/zkfuse/src/zkadapter.cc
index 886051d..93dbef5 100644
--- a/src/contrib/zkfuse/src/zkadapter.cc
+++ b/src/contrib/zkfuse/src/zkadapter.cc
@@ -845,7 +845,10 @@ ZooKeeperAdapter::getNodeData(const string &path,
             string("Unable to get data of node ") + path, rc
         );
     } else {
-        return string( buffer, buffer + len );
+        if (len == -1) {
+            len = 0;
+        };
+        return string( buffer, len );
     }
 }
{code}
